---
# Build-time projection of the per-poll registry (_data/constitutions/<pile>/<poll>.json).
# Renders a small, cacheable, PUBLIC subset of every poll's config — the half a landing
# page needs to render the question, plus the lifecycle window. The judge guidance is
# included because Tell already shows it to respondents (shown_guidance); nothing private
# lives here. No network IO at build. See docs/per-poll-registry.md.
#
# Shape: a flat array of poll objects, each keyed by {pile, poll}. A landing page fetches
# this once and looks up its own {pile, poll} rather than trusting render hints in the QR.
layout: null
permalink: /polls.json
---
{%- comment -%}
  site.data.constitutions is a hash {pile => {poll => config}} (Jekyll namespaces nested
  _data dirs). Liquid has no array push and nested forloop.last is unreliable across two
  levels, so we emit each object with a "|||" terminator, split, then join with commas —
  Ruby's split drops the trailing empty, giving valid JSON with no dangling comma.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- capture rows -%}
{%- for pile in site.data.constitutions -%}
{%- for poll in pile[1] -%}
{%- assign c = poll[1] -%}
{"pile":{{ c.pile | jsonify }},"poll":{{ c.poll | jsonify }},"type":{{ c.type | jsonify }},"text":{{ c.text | jsonify }},"options":{{ c.options | jsonify }},"accept_writein":{{ c.accept_writein | jsonify }},"guidance":{{ c.guidance | jsonify }}{% if c.lifecycle %},"lifecycle":{{ c.lifecycle | jsonify }}{% endif %}}|||
{%- endfor -%}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- endcapture -%}
{%- assign items = rows | split: "|||" -%}
[{{ items | join: "," }}]
